The hall contains a portrait of Elizabeth I, as well as portraits of former principals and benefactors.
Residential accommodation was first built at the sports ground in 1967 (Thelwall House, rebuilt in 1998), with additions between 1988 and 1990 (Hugh Price House and Leoline Jenkins House).
